<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="577" type="taxonomic history">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Taxonomic history.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, P" journalOrPublisher="George Nicol, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" refId="B45" refString="Russell, P, 1796. An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons. George Nicol, London, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" title="An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" year="1796">Russell (1796)</bibRefCitation>
described ' 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Boodroo Pam</emphasis>
' based on a specimen from Vizagapatam (now Vishakhapatnam, Andhra Pradesh state, India) in the northern Eastern Ghats. 
<bibRefCitation author="Shaw, G" journalOrPublisher="Herpetology Notes" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/180016page/7/mode/1up" refId="B51" refString="Shaw, G, 1802. General Zoology, or Systematic Natural History. London: G. Kearsley, Thomas Davison 3 (part 2): 313-615. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/180016page/7/mode/1up" title="General Zoology, or Systematic Natural History. London: G. Kearsley, Thomas Davison 3 (part 2): 313 - 615." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/180016page/7/mode/1up" year="1802">Shaw (1802)</bibRefCitation>
provided a nominate description of that taxon as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Raffles" authorityYear="1822" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coluber gramineus" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gramineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Coluber gramineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on the specimen depicted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, P" journalOrPublisher="George Nicol, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" refId="B45" refString="Russell, P, 1796. An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons. George Nicol, London, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" title="An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" year="1796">Russell (1796)</bibRefCitation>
. Bechestein (1802) erected the nomen 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coluber viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Coluber viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and Daudin (1803) erected the nomen 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daudin" authorityYear="1803" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vipera viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Vipera viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the same specimen depicted in 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, P" journalOrPublisher="George Nicol, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" refId="B45" refString="Russell, P, 1796. An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons. George Nicol, London, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" title="An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" year="1796">Russell (1796)</bibRefCitation>
. These nomina are connected by an objective synonymy and therefore share the same type specimen (see Russell, 1796) and type locality, Vizagapatam. Notwithstanding these, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lacepede, BGEL" journalOrPublisher="Annales du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="184 - 211" publicationUrl="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/29642633" refId="B33" refString="Lacepede, BGEL, 1804. Memoire sur plusieurs animaux de la Nouvelle- Hollande dont la description n'a pas encore ete publiee, Paris. Annales du Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle 4: 184 - 211, http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/29642633" title="Memoire sur plusieurs animaux de la Nouvelle- Hollande dont la description n'a pas encore ete publiee, Paris." url="http://biodiversitylibrary.org/page/29642633" volume="4" year="1804">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
(1804)
</bibRefCitation>
described an Indonesian species as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This nomen 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
, 1804 has now been superseded by its junior subjective synonym 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus insularis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kramer, 1977 that is now in prevailing usage (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2992.1.1" author="David, P" journalOrPublisher="Hamadryad" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B12" refString="David, P, Vogel, G, Dubois, A, 2011. On the need to follow rigorously the Rules of the Code for the subsequent designation of a nucleospecies (type species) for a nominal genus which lacked one: the case of the nominal genus Trimeresurus Lacepede 1804 (Reptilia: Squamata: Viperidae). Zootaxa 2992: 1-51. https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2992.1.1" title="On the need to follow rigorously the Rules of the Code for the subsequent designation of a nucleospecies (type species) for a nominal genus which lacked one: the case of the nominal genus Trimeresurus Lacepede 1804 (Reptilia: Squamata: Viperidae). Zootaxa 2992: 1 - 51." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2992.1.1" year="2011">David et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
). Three unavailable nomina 
<taxonomicName genus="Trigonocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trigonocephalus fario" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="fario">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trigonocephalus fario</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jan, 1859, 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bothrops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothrops viridis subsp. fario" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="viridis" subSpecies="fario">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Bothrops viridis fario</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jan, 1863 and 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Bothrops" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Bothrops viridis subsp. genei" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="viridis" subSpecies="genei">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Bothrops viridis genei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jan, 1863 are present.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
<bibRefCitation author="Jerdon, TC" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="522 - 534" publicationUrl="http://www.southasiaarchive.com/Content/sarf.120250/221450/004" refId="B28" refString="Jerdon, TC, 1854. Catalogue of the Reptiles inhabiting the Peninsula of India, Part 2. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal 22: 522 - 534, http://www.southasiaarchive.com/Content/sarf.120250/221450/004" title="Catalogue of the Reptiles inhabiting the Peninsula of India, Part 2." url="http://www.southasiaarchive.com/Content/sarf.120250/221450/004" volume="22" year="1854">Jerdon (1854)</bibRefCitation>
discusses this taxon under the nomen 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Muller &amp; Schlegel" authorityYear="1842" genus="Trigonocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trigonocephalus (Cophias) viridis" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="viridis" subGenus="Cophias">Trigonocephalus (Cophias) viridis</taxonomicName>
and miscredits it to Merrem. 
<bibRefCitation author="Beddome, RH" journalOrPublisher="Madras Quarterly Journal of Medical Sciences" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="1 - 31" refId="B3" refString="Beddome, RH, 1862. Notes upon the land and freshwater snakes of the Madras Presidency. Madras Quarterly Journal of Medical Sciences 5: 1 - 31" title="Notes upon the land and freshwater snakes of the Madras Presidency." volume="5" year="1862">Beddome (1862)</bibRefCitation>
discusses this taxon in part (specimen from Condipalli hills) under the nomen 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see below). 
<bibRefCitation author="Guenther, ACLG" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Miscellany" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B20" refString="Guenther, ACLG, 1864. . The Reptiles of British India. London Printed by the Ray Society, xxvii + 452 pp." title=". The Reptiles of British India. London Printed by the Ray Society, xxvii + 452 pp." year="1864">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1864)
</bibRefCitation>
discusses unrelated East Asian species from Penang, Mergui, Laos, Khasya, Sikkim, Ladakh and Ningpo. 
<bibRefCitation author="Guenther, ACLG" journalOrPublisher="Zoological Miscellany" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B20" refString="Guenther, ACLG, 1864. . The Reptiles of British India. London Printed by the Ray Society, xxvii + 452 pp." title=". The Reptiles of British India. London Printed by the Ray Society, xxvii + 452 pp." year="1864">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Günther">Guenther</normalizedToken>
(1864)
</bibRefCitation>
questioned if Andaman and Nicobar populations are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName genus="Tri." lsidName="Tri. gramineus" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="gramineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Tri. gramineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
s. auct. but concludes that it could not be ascertained based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Blyth, E" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" pagination="367 - 379" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/123983page/507/mode/1up" refId="B6" refString="Blyth, E, 1846. Notes on the fauna of Nicobar Islands. Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal 15: 367 - 379, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/123983page/507/mode/1up" title="Notes on the fauna of Nicobar Islands." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/123983page/507/mode/1up" volume="15" year="1846">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Blyth’s">Blyth's</normalizedToken>
(1846)
</bibRefCitation>
brief notes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Theobald, W" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Biology and Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25761page/7/mode/1up" refId="B57" refString="Theobald, W, 1876. Descriptive catalogue of the reptiles of British India. Thacker, Spink &amp; Co., British India. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25761page/7/mode/1up" title="Descriptive catalogue of the reptiles of British India. Thacker, Spink &amp; Co., British India." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25761page/7/mode/1up" year="1876">Theobald (1876)</bibRefCitation>
also followed a similar view and refers populations from Sylhet, Burma and Malacca under this name. Subsequently, he maintained the same stance when he mentioned specimens from Sikkim, Khasi hills, Assam, Pegu, Andamans, Bengal and Nepal (Theobald, 1876).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
Later 
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger, GA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25773page/5/mode/1up" refId="B7" refString="Boulenger, GA, 1890. The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma: reptilia and Batrachia. London: Taylor &amp; Francis. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25773page/5/mode/1up" title="The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma: reptilia and Batrachia. London: Taylor &amp; Francis." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25773page/5/mode/1up" year="1890">Boulenger (1890)</bibRefCitation>
, perhaps prompted by earlier works (e.g. Theobald), lumped together several S.E. Asian nomina such as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
, 1804 (see 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2992.1.1" author="David, P" journalOrPublisher="Hamadryad" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B12" refString="David, P, Vogel, G, Dubois, A, 2011. On the need to follow rigorously the Rules of the Code for the subsequent designation of a nucleospecies (type species) for a nominal genus which lacked one: the case of the nominal genus Trimeresurus Lacepede 1804 (Reptilia: Squamata: Viperidae). Zootaxa 2992: 1-51. https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2992.1.1" title="On the need to follow rigorously the Rules of the Code for the subsequent designation of a nucleospecies (type species) for a nominal genus which lacked one: the case of the nominal genus Trimeresurus Lacepede 1804 (Reptilia: Squamata: Viperidae). Zootaxa 2992: 1 - 51." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.2992.1.1" year="2011">David et al. 2011</bibRefCitation>
for its proper explanation), 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cantor" authorityYear="1839" genus="Trigonocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trigonocephalus erythrurus" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="erythrurus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trigonocephalus erythrurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Cantor, 1839, 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus albolabris" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albolabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus albolabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gray, 1842, 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus elegans" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="elegans">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus elegans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gray, 1853 and even a non-green taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stoliczka" authorityYear="1870" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus mutabilis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="mutabilis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus mutabilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Stoliczka, 1870 (see Vogel et al. 2014 for its current status). Stejneger (1907) also followed 
<bibRefCitation author="Boulenger, GA" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Asiatic Society of Bengal" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25773page/5/mode/1up" refId="B7" refString="Boulenger, GA, 1890. The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma: reptilia and Batrachia. London: Taylor &amp; Francis. https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25773page/5/mode/1up" title="The fauna of British India, including Ceylon and Burma: reptilia and Batrachia. London: Taylor &amp; Francis." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/25773page/5/mode/1up" year="1890">Boulenger (1890)</bibRefCitation>
. This diluted and over-circumscribed concept of ' 
<taxonomicName genus="Tri." lsidName="Tri. gramineus" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="gramineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Tri. gramineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
' (sic) encompassing almost all green 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, gave rise to the false notion that it is a very widespread and variable species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="577" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="577">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coluber viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Coluber viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bechestein, 1802 and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Daudin" authorityYear="1803" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Vipera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vipera viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Vipera viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Daudin, 1803 are both objective junior synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Colubridae" genus="Coluber" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coluber viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Coluber viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Shaw, 1802, all being described on the basis of the very same type specimen described and illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Russell, P" journalOrPublisher="George Nicol, London" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" publicationUrl="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" refId="B45" refString="Russell, P, 1796. An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons. George Nicol, London, https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" title="An account of Indian serpents collected on the coast of Coromandel, containing descriptions and drawings of each species, together with experiments and remarks on their several poisons." url="https://www.biodiversitylibrary.org/item/252813page/7/mode/1up" year="1796">Russell (1796)</bibRefCitation>
as &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Boodroo Pam</emphasis>
&quot;. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus viridis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Lacépède">Lacepede</normalizedToken>
, 1804 is a nomen oblitum superseded by 
<taxonomicName class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus insularis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="insularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus insularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Kramer, 1977 that is now in prevailing usage for this Indonesian species (
<bibRefCitation author="Wallach, V" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bombay Natural History Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B64" refString="Wallach, V, Williams, KL, Boundy, J, 2014. Snakes of the World: a Catalogue of Living and Extinct Species. Boca Raton (Florida): CRC Press (Taylor &amp; Francis Group), 1209 pp." title="Snakes of the World: a Catalogue of Living and Extinct Species. Boca Raton (Florida): CRC Press (Taylor &amp; Francis Group), 1209 pp." year="2014">Wallach et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
). Two female paratype specimens from the Eastern Ghats and one male specimen from Matheran, northern Western Ghats of a former subjective junior synonym (fide 
<bibRefCitation author="Wallach, V" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Bombay Natural History Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" refId="B64" refString="Wallach, V, Williams, KL, Boundy, J, 2014. Snakes of the World: a Catalogue of Living and Extinct Species. Boca Raton (Florida): CRC Press (Taylor &amp; Francis Group), 1209 pp." title="Snakes of the World: a Catalogue of Living and Extinct Species. Boca Raton (Florida): CRC Press (Taylor &amp; Francis Group), 1209 pp." year="2014">Wallach et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
) 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mallik &amp; Srikanthan &amp; Ganesh &amp; Vijayakumar &amp; Campbell &amp; Malhotra &amp; Shanker" authorityYear="2021" class="Reptilia" family="Viperidae" genus="Trimeresurus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trimeresurus occidentalis" order="Squamata" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Trimeresurus occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Pope &amp; Pope, 1933 is herein referred to 
<taxonomicName genus="Tri." lsidName="Tri. gramineus" pageId="0" pageNumber="577" rank="species" species="gramineus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="577">Tri. gramineus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Shaw, 1802) with respect to its phylogenetic and morphological affinities.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
